repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body:
By accident, the existing special int object handling code was not used when the result of a comparison was already known to be of type bint (instead of a Python object), nor for the "!=" operator.

It now has a dedicated implementation for (in-)equality.

commit.message:
The optimised int/float comparison was accidentally not activated when the result of a comparison was already known to be of type bint (instead of a Python object), nor for the "!=" operator.
These seem to be fairly common cases.
Give equality comparisons to integer constants a dedicated implementation that minimises branching and comparisons.
Apply some type casts for safety.
Add a debug helper test that prints information about the current C build environment.
Handle integer comparison in the gap between the maximum multiple PyLong digits that fit into a long completely and LONG_MAX.
Fix "buildenv" pseudo-test in Py2.6 (which lacks the PyLong internals)
Repair and simplify unrolled PyLong comparison loop that used PyLong_BASE incorrectly (it's an exponential base, not a factor).

title: Further optimise int/float comparison
